Cell.Text: [S] GS|We will see if you truly have the gift. | Show us, Dragonborn. Let us taste of your Voice.
[S] GS|First, let us see if you truly are Dragonborn. Let us taste of your Voice.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirIntroA2: You call me Dragonborn. What does that mean?

Cell.Text: [S] I am Master Arngeir. I speak for the Greybeards. | Now tell me, Dragonborn, why have you come here?
[S] GS|<<Shared>> So... a Dragonborn appears, at this moment in the turning of the age.
<<Shared>> So... a Dragonborn appears, at this moment in the turning of the age.
G|Shout for us, Dragonborn. Then we may have time for questions.
G|<<Shared>> Strike the targets as they appear. Breath and focus.
G|Stand next to me, and prepare your Whirlwind Sprint. Master Borri will give the signal.
G|Follow me. Master Borri will test your Whirlwind Sprint.
G|We will do your next test in the courtyard. Follow Master Borri.
G|Master Borri will teach you the first Word of a new Shout. Attend to him.
S|Your quick mastery of a new Thu'um is... astonishing. I'd heard the stories of the abilities of Dragonborn, but to see it for myself...

[S] <<Shared>> You are now ready for your last trial. | Retrieve the Horn of Jurgen Windcaller, our founder, from his tomb in the ancient fane of Ustengrav. | Remain true to the Way of the Voice, and you will return.
No. Indeed not. But beware that your skill does not outstrip your wisdom.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirHornA1: I thought it was this easy for everyone.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> You are now ready for your last trial. | Retrieve the Horn of Jurgen Windcaller, our founder, from his tomb in the ancient fane of Ustengrav. | Remain true to the Way of the Voice, and you will return.
[S] G|You've done it. You've retrieved the Horn of Jurgen Windcaller. | Congratulations. You have passed all the trials. | Come with me. It is time for us to recognize you formally as Dragonborn.
G|Stand in the center of the room and prepare yourself to taste the Voice of the Greybeards.
G|Come inside. The other masters will meet us there.
G|First, Master Wulfgar will teach you the final word of Unrelenting Force. You are ready.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirReturnHornTopic: I have the Horn of Jurgen Windcaller.
MQ105ArngeirWhySummonMe: Why did you summon me here?

Cell.Text: We are the Greybeards, followers of the Way of the Voice. | You stand in High Hrothgar, on the slopes of Kynareth's sacred mountain. | Here we commune with the voice of the sky, and strive to achieve balance between our inner and outer selves.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirIntroB1: Who are you? What is this place?

Cell.Text: We are here to guide you in that pursuit, just as the Greybeards have sought to guide those of the Dragon Blood that came before you.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirIntroB2: I want to find out what it means to be Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: We are honored to welcome a Dragonborn to High Hrothgar. | We will do our best to teach you how to use your gift in fulfillment of your destiny.
G|You have shown that you are Dragonborn. You have the inborn gift. | But do you have the discipline and temperament to follow the path laid out for you? That remains to be seen.

You are not the first. There have been many of the Dragon Blood since Akatosh first bestowed that gift upon mortalkind. | Whether you are the only Dragonborn of this age... that is not ours to know. | You are the only one that has been revealed thus far. That is all I can say.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirIntroB2A1: You mean I'm not the only Dragonborn?

Cell.Text: That is for you to discover. We can show you the Way, but not your destination.
The others do not speak. Their Voices are too powerful for you to withstand.
You were given this gift by the gods for a reason. It is up to you to figure out how best to use it.

Node.Caption: MQ105ArngeirHornA3: I don't know how I do it. It just happens.
